9 49-613. PUTTING GLASS OR OTHER INJURIOUS MATERIALS ON HIGHWAY PROHIB-
10 ITED -- SECURED LOADS. (1) The following provisions of this section shall ap-
11 ply to persons and vehicles not otherwise exempted from the application of
12 this section by federal or state law:.
13 (1) (a) No person shall throw or deposit upon any highway any glass bot-
14 tle, glass, nails, tacks, wire, cans, or any other substance likely to
15 injure any person, animal or vehicle upon the highway.
16 (2) (b) Any person who drops, or permits to be dropped or thrown, upon
17 any highway any destructive or injurious material shall immediately re-
18 move that material or cause it to be removed.
19 (3) (c) Any person removing a wrecked or damaged vehicle from a high-
20 way shall remove any glass or other injurious substance dropped upon the
21 highway from that vehicle.
22 (4) (2) No vehicle shall be operated on any public highway unless such
23 vehicle's load is secured to prevent the load from becoming loose, detached
24 or a hazard to other users of the highway.
25 (5) (a) No person may operate on any public highway any vehicle with any
26 load unless the load is secured and such covering as required thereon
27 by this subsection (6) of this section is securely fastened to prevent
28 the covering or load from becoming loose, detached or a hazard to other
29 users of the highway.
30 (6) (b) Any vehicle operating on a paved public highway with a load of
31 dirt, sand, or gravel susceptible to being dropped, blown, spilled,
32 leaked or otherwise escaping therefrom shall be covered so as to prevent
33 spillage. Covering of such loads is not required if six (6) inches of
34 freeboard is maintained.
35 (7) (c) The provisions of subsections (5) and (6) of this section this
36 subsection shall not apply to a:
37 (i) A government, quasi-government, their agents or employees or
38 contractors thereof, in performance of maintenance or construc-
39 tion of, snow removal, or spreading sand on a highway; or
40 (ii) A vehicle hauling hot mix or cold mix asphalt.
41 (8) (d) The provisions of subsections (4), (5) and (6) of this section
42 this subsection shall not apply to vehicles owned by canal companies,

